sp_Load_Orders
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Staging].[sp_Load_Orders]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;

    TRUNCATE TABLE [Staging].[stg_Orders];

    INSERT INTO [Staging].[stg_Orders]
    SELECT o.OrderID, o.CustomerID, o.OrderDate, o.TotalAmount
    FROM [Sales].[Orders] o
    INNER JOIN [Sales].[Customers] c ON o.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE o.OrderDate >= DATEADD(YEAR, -2, GETDATE());
END

sp_Enrich_Customers
description: Enrich customer data with order metrics
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Transform].[sp_Enrich_Customers]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;

    TRUNCATE TABLE [Transform].[trf_Customer_Enriched];

    INSERT INTO [Transform].[trf_Customer_Enriched]
    SELECT
        c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName, c.Region,
        COUNT(o.OrderID) AS TotalOrders,
        SUM(o.TotalAmount) AS LifetimeValue,
        MAX(o.OrderDate) AS LastOrderDate
    FROM [Staging].[stg_Customers] c
    LEFT JOIN [Staging].[stg_Orders] o ON c.CustomerID = o.CustomerID
    GROUP BY c.CustomerID, c.CustomerName, c.Region;
END

name: sp_Calculate_Order_Metrics
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Transform].[sp_Calculate_Order_Metrics]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;

    TRUNCATE TABLE [Transform].[trf_Order_Metrics];

    INSERT INTO [Transform].[trf_Order_Metrics]
    SELECT
        CAST(OrderDate AS DATE) AS OrderDate,
        COUNT(*) AS OrderCount,
        SUM(TotalAmount) AS Revenue,
        AVG(TotalAmount) AS AvgOrderValue
    FROM [Staging].[stg_Orders]
    GROUP BY CAST(OrderDate AS DATE);
END

name: sp_Load_Dim_Customer
description: Load customer dimension using SCD Type 1
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Analytics].[sp_Load_Dim_Customer]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;

    MERGE [Analytics].[Dim_Customer] AS target
    USING [Transform].[trf_Customer_Enriched] AS source
    ON target.CustomerID = source.CustomerID
    WHEN MATCHED THEN
        UPDATE SET CustomerName = source.CustomerName, Region = source.Region
    WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
        INSERT (CustomerID, CustomerName, Region, TotalOrders, LifetimeValue)
        VALUES (source.CustomerID, source.CustomerName, source.Region, source.TotalOrders, source.LifetimeValue);
END

name: sp_Load_Fact_Sales
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Analytics].[sp_Load_Fact_Sales]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;

    INSERT INTO [Analytics].[Fact_Sales]
    SELECT
        o.OrderID, dc.CustomerKey, dp.ProductKey, dd.DateKey, dr.RegionKey,
        oi.Quantity, oi.UnitPrice, oi.TotalAmount
    FROM [Staging].[stg_Orders] o
    INNER JOIN [Staging].[stg_OrderItems] oi ON o.OrderID = oi.OrderID
    INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Customer] dc ON o.CustomerID = dc.CustomerID
    INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Product] dp ON oi.ProductID = dp.ProductID
    INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Date] dd ON CAST(o.OrderDate AS DATE) = dd.Date
    INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Region] dr ON dc.Region = dr.RegionName
    WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM [Analytics].[Fact_Sales] f WHERE f.OrderID = o.OrderID);
END

name: vw_Sales_Summary
description: Sales summary by customer and product
ddl_text:
CREATE VIEW [Analytics].[vw_Sales_Summary]
AS
SELECT
    dc.CustomerName, dp.ProductName, dd.Year, dd.Month,
    SUM(fs.TotalAmount) AS TotalSales,
    COUNT(*) AS TransactionCount
FROM [Analytics].[Fact_Sales] fs
INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Customer] dc ON fs.CustomerKey = dc.CustomerKey
INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Product] dp ON fs.ProductKey = dp.ProductKey
INNER JOIN [Analytics].[Dim_Date] dd ON fs.DateKey = dd.DateKey
GROUP BY dc.CustomerName, dp.ProductName, dd.Year, dd.Month

name: vw_Top_Customers
ddl_text:
CREATE VIEW [Analytics].[vw_Top_Customers]
AS
SELECT TOP 100
    dc.CustomerID, dc.CustomerName, dc.Region, dc.LifetimeValue,
    RANK() OVER (ORDER BY dc.LifetimeValue DESC) AS CustomerRank
FROM [Analytics].[Dim_Customer] dc
WHERE dc.LifetimeValue > 0
ORDER BY dc.LifetimeValue DESC

name: sp_Build_Org_Hierarchy
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [HR].[sp_Build_Org_Hierarchy]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;

    ;WITH OrgCTE AS (
        SELECT EmployeeID, ManagerID, EmployeeName, 0 AS Level,
               CAST(EmployeeName AS VARCHAR(MAX)) AS HierarchyPath
        FROM [HR].[Employees]
        WHERE ManagerID IS NULL

        UNION ALL

        SELECT e.EmployeeID, e.ManagerID, e.EmployeeName, cte.Level + 1,
               CAST(cte.HierarchyPath + ' > ' + e.EmployeeName AS VARCHAR(MAX))
        FROM [HR].[Employees] e
        INNER JOIN OrgCTE cte ON e.ManagerID = cte.EmployeeID
    )
    SELECT * FROM OrgCTE;
END

name: fn_Calculate_Lead_Score
description: Calculate lead score based on engagement
ddl_text:
CREATE FUNCTION [dbo].[fn_Calculate_Lead_Score](@LeadID INT)
RETURNS INT
AS
BEGIN
    DECLARE @Score INT = 0;

    SELECT @Score =
        CASE WHEN EmailOpens > 10 THEN 30 WHEN EmailOpens > 5 THEN 20 ELSE 10 END +
        CASE WHEN WebsiteVisits > 20 THEN 40 WHEN WebsiteVisits > 10 THEN 25 ELSE 10 END +
        CASE WHEN DemoRequested = 1 THEN 30 ELSE 0 END
    FROM [Marketing].[Leads]
    WHERE LeadID = @LeadID;

    RETURN ISNULL(@Score, 0);
END

name: sp_Segment_Customers
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Transform].[sp_Segment_Customers]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;
    TRUNCATE TABLE [Transform].[trf_Customer_Segments];
    INSERT INTO [Transform].[trf_Customer_Segments]
    SELECT
        c.CustomerID,
        CASE
            WHEN c.LifetimeValue > 10000 THEN 'Platinum'
            WHEN c.LifetimeValue > 5000 THEN 'Gold'
            WHEN c.LifetimeValue > 1000 THEN 'Silver'
            ELSE 'Bronze'
        END AS Segment
    FROM [Transform].[trf_Customer_Enriched] c;
END

name: sp_Analyze_Returns
ddl_text:
CREATE PROCEDURE [Transform].[sp_Analyze_Returns]
AS
BEGIN
    SET NOCOUNT ON;
    INSERT INTO [Transform].[trf_Return_Analysis]
    SELECT
        p.ProductID, p.ProductName,
        COUNT(*) AS ReturnCount,
        AVG(r.Quantity) AS AvgReturnQty
    FROM [Staging].[stg_Returns] r
    INNER JOIN [Staging].[stg_Products] p ON r.ProductID = p.ProductID
    GROUP BY p.ProductID, p.ProductName;
END

name: fn_Calculate_Margin
ddl_text:
CREATE FUNCTION [dbo].[fn_Calculate_Margin](@Price DECIMAL(18,2), @Cost DECIMAL(18,2))
RETURNS DECIMAL(5,2)
AS
BEGIN
    IF @Price = 0 RETURN 0;
    RETURN ((@Price - @Cost) / @Price) * 100;
END
